                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " data for reaction",
                "Sn-120(p,n)Sb-120-g were revised."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The self-supporting metallic foils of (3-6) mg/cm2",
                "thickness and 22 mm diameter made from enriched tin",
                "isotopes by electrolitic deposition technique.",
                "Enrichment of the targets were: 115Sn -51,2%,",
                "116Sn-92,8%,120Sn-96,5%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The efficiency calibration was done using the",
                "standard radioactive sources 22Na,57Co, 60Co, 65Zn,",
                "113Sn, 137Cs and 241Am."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "LINAC"
                ],
                "institute": "4UKRKFT"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "*By authors*. The energy was decreased with pure",
                "aluminum foils-absorbers and, within small limits, also",
                "by the method of energy variation of linear accelerator",
                "beams. The energy losses in the Al absorbers and tin",
                "targets were determined by a code calculating the",
                "energy degradation using the range-energy relation.",
                "*By compiler*. Sn-120(p,n)Sb-120-g was corrected by",
                "authors through adoption of a new branching ratio for",
                "the 1171 keV gamma-transition: Igamma=1.69%,",
                "delta-Igamma=0.09%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "BCINT",
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                " The beam current was measured with the charge",
                "integrator and typically amounted to 100-150 nA."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SITA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "STTA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "for the production cross sections of the 120mSb",
                "isomer, irradiation time 8 hours."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The typical total root-mean-squared",
                "uncertainty of each experimental cross section",
                "resulting from all individual errors (the density of",
                "target nuclei, incident proton beam current, detector",
                "efficiency,"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": 7.0,
                "maximum_value": 13.0,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " counting statistics and decay data) was",
                "7-13%, for the reaction 116Sn(p,n)116Sb at the lowest",
                "energy point 30%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "DECAY"
              ],
